@lars-petter-hauge commented on [Wed Jan 23 2019](https://github.com/equinor/scout/issues/43)

Consider a set of 10 realizations, where nr. 5 fails. If the fifth realization is restarted, check that the values for the parameterization is sane and not e.g. the same as realization 0. 

---

@ManInFez commented on [Thu Nov 21 2019](https://github.com/equinor/scout/issues/43#issuecomment-557086762)

When running ensemble_experiment with a fixed random seed, the parameterization is the same for each time you run the ensemble. However, if you restart a realization, it resamples the prior. More investigation is needed as to why this is happening. As of now, clicking restart results in non-reproducible results

